ZCZC GE27
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 032300 UTC
A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE 977 TO
THE S OF ICELAND WILL WEAKEN AND EXTEND GRADUALLY S AND
EWARDS LATE ON TUESDAY AND EARLY WEDNESDAY AND THEN
BECOME SLOW MOV ACROSS ICELAND THE UK AND WERN
SCANDINAVIA THROUGH THE REMAINDER OF THE PERIOD
DEVELOPING SEVERAL TRANSIENT CENTRES. AN ASSOCIATED
FRONTAL TROUGH WILL MOV NE ACROSS THE CULLERCOATS AREA
REACHING DOVER AND WIGHT EARLY TUESDAY AND VIKING AND
FAIR ISLE LATE TUESDAY. THIS FOLLOWED BY A SECOND FRONTAL
TROUGH WHICH WILL MOV NEWARD DURING WEDNESDAY. A RISK OF
STRG WINDS AT TIMES IN NENRN VIKING AND FAIR ISLE LATE
MONDAY AND EARLY TUESDAY. STRG WINDS MOV ACROSS SERN
PARTS OF GERMAN BIGHT HUMBER THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT
EARLY WEDNESDAY GENERALLY MODERATING LATE WEDNESDAY BUT
OCCASIONAL STRG WINDS CONTINUING IN GERMAN BIGHT HUMBER
THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT BEFORE EASING LATE THURSDAY.
